reviewText: Attack of the 60 Foot Centerfold is the best dang movie I've seen in five days. It is a brilliant B-movie directed by Fred Olen Ray, who has directed like 100 B-movies. And most of them that I've seen have rocked! Attack of the 60 Foot Centerfold is no different, and might be the best dang Fred Olen Ray movie I've seen. I think it is even better than Hollywood Chainsaw Hookers. It has plenty of dang nudity, comedy, and action. If you are a dang B-movie fanatic, you have to see this!

reviewText: Attack Of the 60 Foot Centerfold(BTW, is neither a sequel or remake of the 1958 cult classic Attack of the 50 Foot Woman)is both sexy and hilarious. J.J. North stars as the sweet and alluring model who took part in a experiment to enhance her breasts. What she did not know is that the serum she drank turned her into a giant beauty! The fight sequence with North and another giant supermodel(who drank the serum herself)was a real gem. Although it is Rated R for nudity(as the DVD case says), expect some crude adult humor, mild language and violence. This is an absolute B-movie spectacular!
summary: One Of The Funniest B-Movies I've Ever Seen!

reviewText: This movie was directed by Fred Olen Ray, who has directed such classic films as "Bikini Drive-In" (1995), "Thirteen Erotic Ghosts" (2002), and "Baby Dolls Behind Bars" (2012).  In this movie, the fictitious finalists for "Centerfold Of The Year" are blonde bombshell Angel Grace (J.J. North), ravishing redhead Betty (Tammy Parks), and sexy Inga (Raelyn Saalman).  J.J. North is drop dead gorgeous, yet worried about her attractiveness as she's aging.  She takes part in a secret beauty enhancement program, conducted by Dr. Lindstrom (John Lazar), and Dr. Joyce Mann (Michelle Bauer).  Insecure about her looks and desperate to win the coveted Centerfold, Angel drinks too much of the beauty enhancement formula, and grows to 60-feet tall!  Later, Betty discovers Angel's secret, and overdoses on the formula, causing her to grow into a 60-foot tall gorgeous giant.  Angel and Betty battle it out in one of the greatest catfights ever filmed, outside of a Women-In-Prison movie.  This movie strikes just the right balance of eroticism and humor, and is my favorite Fred Olen Ray film.  Also appearing in this film are Nikki Fritz (“Curse Of The Erotic Tiki”), Jay Richardson ("Hollywood Chainsaw Hookers"), Russ Tamblyn ("Django Unchained"), Ross Hagen ("Fugitive Rage"), and Tommy Kirk ("Mars Needs Women").

reviewText: Great to see a movie that, I myself have had a fantasy of ever since I was like maybe twelve years old. Better than HBO's remake of the '50's thriller 'Attack Of The Fifty Foot Woman' mostly because of the total nudity. Angel ( J. J. North), a simply die-for gorgeous curvy blonde unknowingly overdoses on some concocted beauty-enhancing liquid. She soon wakes up realizing that she is now sixty feet tall. Problem is there are no clothes large enough to fit her, so she's forced to walk around in the buff. Most movie fans may not enjoy this, saying that it's just too weird for them to grasp. Most memorable scene is when one of the other three beauties, Betty (Tammy Parks) a revenge seeking rival of Angel's drinks some of the same liquid and the two girls are dressed in shrouds having a brawl in a city street. Great entertainment here, as far as I'm concerned. Recommended.
summary: 'Attack Of The 60 Foot Centerfold' (New Concorde) Time: 84 min.
